race.description: Cressy Chaff Cutters Longford Cup 1st Jan Hcp
race.comment: SNOWDONIA (3) went close here first up and then settled well back off the 13 gate at Hobart and found one much too good. She will be fitter again and is still well shy of her best. She can find that form this evening. BUNKER JAKO (1) brought strong form and trials to resumption, and things didn't work out for the speedy galloper. He's right up to this with the extra fitness and sharp improvement is on the cards. STREETFIGHTER VEGA (6) resumed over 1400m off a try in an Open 3 at Moonee Valley (Victoria) and the fitness gave out despite strong market support. The blinkers are on for the first time, and he's thrown in with the 4kg claim. Needs a good ride, but he will have come on and is well in the mix. CELTIC ROSE (11) peaks and is heading in the right direction. A leading hoop will use the inside gate and give her every chance.
